SIMPLE: supererogate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supererogate
<hw>Su`per*er"o*gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Supererogated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Supererogating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>supererogatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>supererogare</ets> to spend or
pay out over and above; <ets>super</ets> over, above +
<ets>erogare</ets> to expend or pay out money from the public treasury
after asking the consent of the people. See <er>Super-</er>, and
<er>Erogate</er>, <er>Rogation</er>.]</ety> <def>To do more than duty
requires; to perform works of supererogation; to atone (for a dificiency
in another) by means of a surplus action or quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fervency of one man in prayer can not <qex>supererogate</qex>
for the coldness of another.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supererogation</ent>⟦br⟧
